1
00:01:01,228 --> 00:01:02,730
[pensive music plays]

2
00:01:19,622 --> 00:01:21,373
[Woo-seok]
<i>What are you doing? Are you crazy?</i>

3
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:26,921
<i>If I could just disappear,</i>
<i>it would all be over!</i>

4
00:01:27,004 --> 00:01:30,925
I want to die.
Why are you stopping me? Why?

5
00:01:31,008 --> 00:01:32,676
Why are you doing this to me?

6
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:34,470
What do you want to know?

7
00:01:34,553 --> 00:01:35,721
You.

8
00:01:36,847 --> 00:01:38,891
Han Seol-ah, I want to know you.

9
00:01:48,609 --> 00:01:51,195
[sighs] It bothers me…

10
00:01:56,242 --> 00:01:58,619
{\an8}EPISODE 5

11
00:02:23,936 --> 00:02:25,229
{\an8}[ringing tone]

12
00:02:26,772 --> 00:02:30,192
{\an8}Mr. Do Eun-hyuk?
I'd like to meet with you.

13
00:02:30,276 --> 00:02:33,737
{\an8}I have nothing more to say to you.
I'm hanging up.

14
00:02:39,994 --> 00:02:41,161
[sighs]

15
00:02:41,954 --> 00:02:43,455
[dramatic music plays]

16
00:02:54,508 --> 00:02:57,261
How far can a string
of unfortunate events go?

17
00:02:57,970 --> 00:02:59,096
A coworker.

18
00:02:59,179 --> 00:03:00,723
An ex-boyfriend.

19
00:03:02,433 --> 00:03:03,934
And your parents too.

20
00:03:21,535 --> 00:03:23,579
{\an8}SALES CONSIGNMENT PROPOSAL

21
00:03:23,662 --> 00:03:26,040
6-WEEK EXECUTION ROAD MAP

22
00:03:26,123 --> 00:03:28,334
RISK MANAGEMENT & PARTNERSHIP STRATEGY

23
00:03:37,301 --> 00:03:40,721
Well, you'd be hard-pressed
to receive a better offer than this.

24
00:03:40,804 --> 00:03:42,681
I understand your concerns,

25
00:03:42,765 --> 00:03:45,684
since a Stiller piece
isn't everyone's expertise,

26
00:03:45,768 --> 00:03:47,686
but we'll lock in that final price,

27
00:03:47,770 --> 00:03:50,522
even if we need a house bidder to do so.

28
00:03:51,273 --> 00:03:55,194
If I consign this piece to you,
what happens to Ms. Han then?

29
00:03:56,654 --> 00:03:59,073
Well… as I'm sure you're aware,

30
00:03:59,156 --> 00:04:01,283
Ms. Han has had a few issues lately.

31
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:04,536
She won't be in that position
much longer anyway,

32
00:04:04,620 --> 00:04:08,248
and so you should work with someone
you'll be dealing with long-term.

33
00:04:08,332 --> 00:04:09,917
Oh, I see.

34
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,629
You're trying to take this opportunity
to crush her, aren't you?

35
00:04:14,338 --> 00:04:16,757
Well, that's how this business works,
doesn't it?

36
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:18,884
[scoffs] That's cutthroat.

37
00:04:20,302 --> 00:04:23,597
Is this why Ms. Han agreed
to do me that favor?

38
00:04:26,183 --> 00:04:27,977
[whimsical music plays]

39
00:04:29,853 --> 00:04:33,107
Oh, oops.
Looks like the meetings overlapped.

40
00:04:36,944 --> 00:04:38,320
Since this has happened…

41
00:04:40,364 --> 00:04:42,116
why don't we get this sorted out?

42
00:04:46,495 --> 00:04:48,455
I'm working to launch a new venture

43
00:04:48,539 --> 00:04:50,749
that enables co-buying of artworks
through Fintech.

44
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:52,126
BUSINESS PLAN
YOUR ARTWORK

45
00:04:52,209 --> 00:04:54,795
I needed an expert for guidance
on the lineup,

46
00:04:55,629 --> 00:04:57,548
and Ms. Han agreed to take charge.

47
00:04:59,341 --> 00:05:03,012
Chair Kim also encouraged me
to give it my best shot.

48
00:05:05,931 --> 00:05:08,559
I need to return the favor, so…

49
00:05:08,642 --> 00:05:11,020
You understand my position, right?

50
00:05:13,605 --> 00:05:15,024
Yes, of course.

51
00:05:24,116 --> 00:05:28,078
[breathes deeply]
Those two are ganging up on me.

52
00:05:33,375 --> 00:05:35,377
If I may take this further,

53
00:05:35,461 --> 00:05:38,172
I'd like to get something even bigger
than just consulting.

54
00:05:38,255 --> 00:05:44,428
How about you take the lead as the head of
the "Your Artwork" venture from now on?

55
00:05:45,888 --> 00:05:50,559
Thank you for the offer, but I have
something I must attend to at Royal.

56
00:05:52,311 --> 00:05:57,149
I can give you 5% in stock options,
along with twice your current salary.

57
00:05:58,275 --> 00:06:00,402
I won't be easily swayed by money.

58
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:07,201
Ah, neither honor nor money.

59
00:06:08,035 --> 00:06:09,536
Then what is it?

60
00:06:10,287 --> 00:06:12,456
What exactly are you after, Seol-ah?

61
00:06:15,084 --> 00:06:16,877
[ominous music plays]

62
00:06:21,799 --> 00:06:23,717
[pensive music plays]

63
00:06:28,222 --> 00:06:31,266
[Eun-hye] <i>It was a famous case,</i>
<i>the Cheongun deadly family fire.</i>

64
00:06:31,934 --> 00:06:35,312
<i>Han Seol-ah was the only one who survived.</i>

65
00:06:35,896 --> 00:06:40,192
[no audible dialogue]

66
00:06:56,542 --> 00:06:59,920
[no audible dialogue]

67
00:07:05,342 --> 00:07:08,220
Excuse me. Oh, yes, hello.
Do you remember anything about this?

68
00:07:08,303 --> 00:07:09,847
CHEONGUN FIRE KILLS COUPLE IN THEIR 40S,
LEAVES TEENAGE DAUGHTER CRITICALLY INJURED

69
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:12,349
- Oh, this? Yeah, there was a big fire.
- Do you know where this was?

70
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:14,685
Yes, over there. It was huge.

71
00:07:23,735 --> 00:07:25,195
I thought you wouldn't come

72
00:07:25,279 --> 00:07:27,364
I only came
because I knew you'd stir everything up.

73
00:07:28,824 --> 00:07:32,286
Do you know how hard Seol-ah
has tried to put all this behind her?

74
00:07:33,412 --> 00:07:37,249
Digging up the past like this
is just torture for her.

75
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:39,626
Then why don't you just tell me?

76
00:07:39,710 --> 00:07:41,753
I don't wanna rely on old news articles

77
00:07:41,837 --> 00:07:44,882
or the neighbors' fading memories.
You tell me, Mr. Do.

78
00:07:44,965 --> 00:07:46,842
I don't want to torture anyone, either.

79
00:08:21,335 --> 00:08:22,461
Have a seat.

80
00:08:56,078 --> 00:08:57,079
It's ginger tea.

81
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:02,334
When you work in cold water
for a long time, your body gets stiff.

82
00:09:03,502 --> 00:09:05,337
Now I drink this out of habit.

83
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,352
Her father was…

84
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:25,857
a poor artist
who worked out of a small back room.

85
00:09:28,318 --> 00:09:32,489
He struggled so much
that he borrowed from loan sharks.

86
00:09:33,282 --> 00:09:36,827
[sobs] Please, I'm begging you.
Don't do this.

87
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:40,330
What'd you think? That we wouldn't
be able to find you if you ran?

88
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:45,085
No, sir. Please, sir.

89
00:09:45,168 --> 00:09:47,462
[sobs] I'm sorry. Please, I'm sorry.

90
00:09:48,964 --> 00:09:53,218
Oh. Oh, no!
Please don't touch him. Please.

91
00:09:53,302 --> 00:09:57,472
I'll take the punishment.
Do it to me. Do it to me!

92
00:09:57,556 --> 00:10:01,226
- Do it to me! Please! Please!
- Please, sir, don't do this.

93
00:10:02,269 --> 00:10:03,729
<i>She didn't cry.</i>

94
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:09,109
She endured the whole thing
without letting out a single scream.

95
00:10:10,527 --> 00:10:12,195
While I watched from outside,

96
00:10:13,822 --> 00:10:15,741
clenching my teeth till they'd break.

97
00:10:17,492 --> 00:10:18,952
Seol-ah just…

98
00:10:20,454 --> 00:10:21,955
endured it.

99
00:10:27,753 --> 00:10:29,796
Shortly after that, the fire broke out.

100
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:34,134
He figured
they might as well all die together.

101
00:10:35,844 --> 00:10:37,679
And the child survived alone.

102
00:10:39,222 --> 00:10:41,183
She survived, but it wasn't living,

103
00:10:42,893 --> 00:10:47,147
not after seeing her family burn
before her eyes.

104
00:10:51,693 --> 00:10:53,570
And you couldn't turn your back on her.

105
00:10:56,531 --> 00:10:58,450
So, you've been by her side ever since?

106
00:11:01,328 --> 00:11:02,454
That is quite a friendship.

107
00:11:04,498 --> 00:11:07,751
Or, should I call it love?

108
00:11:12,631 --> 00:11:13,799
[Eun-hyuk sighs]

109
00:11:15,509 --> 00:11:18,970
Don't act like you understand
everything that we've been through.

110
00:11:20,055 --> 00:11:23,517
Our relationship isn't something
you can just reduce to labels

111
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,185
like friendship or love.

112
00:11:26,353 --> 00:11:27,729
Let's end this here.

113
00:11:27,813 --> 00:11:31,983
About Seol-ah, stop misjudging her
and stop bothering her.

114
00:11:45,288 --> 00:11:47,290
{\an8}[Gounod's "Je Veux Vivre" plays]

115
00:11:58,718 --> 00:12:02,055
Emil Stiller has been confirmed
as the main piece.

116
00:12:04,182 --> 00:12:05,183
Stiller?

117
00:12:07,436 --> 00:12:11,189
Are we aiming
for the highest bid this time?

118
00:12:11,273 --> 00:12:12,482
We should.

119
00:12:14,484 --> 00:12:17,529
When someone puts their whole heart
into something,

120
00:12:17,612 --> 00:12:20,115
the universe just responds.

121
00:12:21,241 --> 00:12:25,537
Well, that must be why all the finest
artworks find their way to you, ma'am.

122
00:12:26,538 --> 00:12:28,081
True effort

123
00:12:29,416 --> 00:12:31,626
always adds up in one way or another.

124
00:12:33,295 --> 00:12:37,632
We have a long way to go
before I'm satisfied.

125
00:12:45,557 --> 00:12:47,309
You should get back to work.

126
00:12:49,352 --> 00:12:50,520
Ma'am.

127
00:13:00,572 --> 00:13:02,657
{\an8}- So distracting.
- [music stops]

128
00:13:04,201 --> 00:13:05,202
[sighs]

129
00:13:07,579 --> 00:13:08,914
<i>Oh, life</i>

130
00:13:09,748 --> 00:13:12,000
<i>Running through</i>

131
00:13:14,753 --> 00:13:16,463
<i>The vast, desolate wilderness</i>

132
00:13:17,255 --> 00:13:20,217
[continues humming melody]

133
00:13:42,155 --> 00:13:43,823
[lock clicking]

134
00:14:36,751 --> 00:14:37,877
[sighs]

135
00:14:39,921 --> 00:14:41,590
I'll have a glass of this.

136
00:14:49,723 --> 00:14:50,807
May I join you?

137
00:14:53,977 --> 00:14:55,520
[jazz playing]

138
00:14:57,230 --> 00:15:00,400
Well, since you already know about
what happened with her parents,

139
00:15:00,483 --> 00:15:01,985
there's nothing left to hide.

140
00:15:02,068 --> 00:15:05,238
Yeah, that's when Seol-ah
started staying at our place.

141
00:15:05,322 --> 00:15:07,073
I was her senior in high school

142
00:15:07,157 --> 00:15:10,118
and I bombed the college entrance exam,
so I never went to college,

143
00:15:10,201 --> 00:15:11,911
but I've been looking out for her
ever since.

144
00:15:11,995 --> 00:15:14,497
So it's not an ordinary connection.

145
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:18,418
So I take it that you two are very close.

146
00:15:18,501 --> 00:15:22,714
I think we are, but she's not the type
to just lay her heart completely bare.

147
00:15:23,965 --> 00:15:26,384
Maybe it's because
she's been hurt so much.

148
00:15:26,468 --> 00:15:29,888
When she's sad or in pain,
she just hides it.

149
00:15:30,847 --> 00:15:33,767
That's why people misunderstand her.

150
00:15:40,357 --> 00:15:42,067
Mr. Do Eun-hyuk said the same.

151
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:44,903
He told me not to bother Han Seol-ah.

152
00:15:44,986 --> 00:15:46,488
She's not like that.

153
00:15:47,072 --> 00:15:48,782
She just wouldn't commit insurance fraud.

154
00:15:48,865 --> 00:15:52,619
She became an orphan at 15,
lost her first love in an accident,

155
00:15:52,702 --> 00:15:54,913
and she even had to see a psychiatrist…

156
00:15:57,165 --> 00:15:58,166
[sighs]

157
00:16:01,628 --> 00:16:03,713
Was Mr. Lee Su-ho's death hard for her?

158
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:08,468
After he died in that accident,
she started relying on meds,

159
00:16:08,551 --> 00:16:10,053
and now she feels nothing.

160
00:16:11,221 --> 00:16:13,139
[sighs deeply] That poor thing.

161
00:16:13,223 --> 00:16:15,100
She's had the worst luck.

162
00:16:19,771 --> 00:16:24,901
And why did you open your bar here,
next to the auction house?

163
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:26,111
Sorry?

164
00:16:29,447 --> 00:16:32,117
I figured it'd be smart
to cater drinks to the auction house,

165
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:35,120
maybe even meet a good guy along the way…

166
00:16:35,203 --> 00:16:36,204
[sighs]

167
00:16:37,664 --> 00:16:39,290
Why am I even saying all this?

168
00:16:43,461 --> 00:16:45,922
You must've been hungry.
I'll get you some more.

169
00:16:51,594 --> 00:16:54,556
[scoffs] Didn't even touch it.

170
00:17:00,645 --> 00:17:02,772
[melancholy music plays]

171
00:17:09,320 --> 00:17:12,115
If I could just disappear,
it would all be over.

172
00:17:12,198 --> 00:17:13,867
I don't care anymore!

173
00:17:13,950 --> 00:17:17,287
<i>I want to die.</i>
<i>Why are you stopping me? Why?</i>

174
00:17:39,768 --> 00:17:41,811
{\an8}HAN SEOL-AH(38).M4A

175
00:17:47,484 --> 00:17:49,152
[Eun-hyuk] Staying up all night?

176
00:17:52,489 --> 00:17:54,949
Even if I go home,
I won't get any sleep anyway.

177
00:17:55,909 --> 00:17:59,954
His work is so realistic,
it actually freaks me out a bit.

178
00:18:00,997 --> 00:18:02,165
Exactly why I look at it.

179
00:18:03,458 --> 00:18:08,213
If I face the horrible reality head-on,
it feels like nothing can get worse.

180
00:18:09,839 --> 00:18:13,927
When I sleep,
that day keeps replaying in my dreams.

181
00:18:15,428 --> 00:18:19,516
[Seol-ah, through earbuds]
<i>The dock, the last time I saw him.</i>

182
00:18:19,599 --> 00:18:22,519
<i>Waking up makes it even more terrifying</i>

183
00:18:22,602 --> 00:18:24,646
<i>because I know it actually happened.</i>

184
00:18:25,939 --> 00:18:27,982
[Eun-hyuk, through earbuds]
<i>Seol-ah, what can I do for you?</i>

185
00:18:28,066 --> 00:18:30,276
<i>Want to take a day off?</i>

186
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:32,529
<i>Should Suk-ji and I stay with you?</i>

187
00:18:34,072 --> 00:18:35,615
I'll let you know if it gets too hard.

188
00:18:36,908 --> 00:18:42,372
All I can do is just stay right by
your side, and that's so frustrating.

189
00:18:42,455 --> 00:18:44,123
That's how I get through it,

190
00:18:44,207 --> 00:18:48,711
because you're there. You stay by my side.

191
00:18:48,795 --> 00:18:50,839
That's what keeps me going.

192
00:19:44,517 --> 00:19:45,685
[sighs]

193
00:19:46,895 --> 00:19:48,396
Isn't she cold?

194
00:20:00,617 --> 00:20:02,827
[tense music plays]

195
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:28,561
[sighs]

196
00:20:30,521 --> 00:20:33,232
[sighs] What the hell am I doing?

197
00:20:51,459 --> 00:20:52,961
{\an8}[upbeat music plays]

198
00:20:53,044 --> 00:20:55,171
CAPTURING LIGHT:
KIM JOON-YOUNG SPECIAL EXHIBITION

199
00:21:22,949 --> 00:21:27,286
{\an8}THIS GLASS SCULPTURE EVOKES A SINGLE BLOOM
EMERGING IN THE STILLNESS OF NIGHT

200
00:21:33,167 --> 00:21:36,838
- [employee 1] What was that?
- [employee 2] Oh, no! What happened?

201
00:21:39,716 --> 00:21:41,467
[employees murmuring]

202
00:21:42,719 --> 00:21:45,304
I'm sorry. It slipped from my hands.

203
00:21:46,597 --> 00:21:48,182
[tense music plays]

204
00:21:49,809 --> 00:21:51,060
Are you okay though?

205
00:21:52,729 --> 00:21:56,441
- Yes.
- Oh, man. This is the main piece.

206
00:21:56,524 --> 00:21:57,775
What do we do now?

207
00:21:57,859 --> 00:22:01,195
- The opening's in just two days…
- Are you crazy?

208
00:22:01,279 --> 00:22:02,864
What are you gonna do now?

209
00:22:02,947 --> 00:22:04,532
Do you even know how much this is worth?

210
00:22:04,615 --> 00:22:05,616
Na-hee.

211
00:22:08,119 --> 00:22:10,329
I'm sorry, Ms. Han. I'm sorry.

212
00:22:11,497 --> 00:22:15,043
First, leave everything as is
and get the claim started.

213
00:22:15,126 --> 00:22:16,461
Sure.

214
00:22:17,295 --> 00:22:19,714
And you, Ms. Do Eun-hye.
I need a word with you.

215
00:22:23,926 --> 00:22:25,845
[Tae-seok] Wow…

216
00:22:25,928 --> 00:22:27,513
Whoa.

217
00:22:28,514 --> 00:22:30,183
It was a mistake, right?

218
00:22:31,142 --> 00:22:32,602
Think whatever you want.

219
00:22:36,189 --> 00:22:37,857
Was it intentional?

220
00:22:40,359 --> 00:22:42,695
You have a hunch, but no evidence.

221
00:22:42,779 --> 00:22:44,489
And you're pissed.

222
00:22:44,572 --> 00:22:46,449
I felt exactly the same way.

223
00:22:46,532 --> 00:22:49,327
My brother Seung-jae and Ms. Kim
were both killed

224
00:22:49,410 --> 00:22:51,037
but there's no evidence.

225
00:22:52,705 --> 00:22:54,707
You're really delusional.

226
00:22:55,374 --> 00:22:57,668
What? "Delusional"?

227
00:22:57,752 --> 00:23:01,172
I don't care whether you report me
or go public, but this is unacceptable.

228
00:23:01,255 --> 00:23:02,590
Understood?

229
00:23:03,216 --> 00:23:05,218
How can someone who studied art
do such a thing?

230
00:23:06,052 --> 00:23:08,471
We handle artworks
as if they were our lives.

231
00:23:08,554 --> 00:23:12,016
And you call yourself a specialist
but you can't even show them respect.

232
00:23:13,976 --> 00:23:16,270
Think about whether
you even deserve that title.

233
00:23:16,354 --> 00:23:18,356
Then fire me.

234
00:23:37,625 --> 00:23:41,045
I'm really sorry, Mr. Kim.
Even if we have to push the schedule,

235
00:23:41,129 --> 00:23:42,964
- we'll--
- [line disconnects]

236
00:23:43,047 --> 00:23:45,550
Mr. Kim. Mr. Kim?

237
00:23:54,517 --> 00:23:55,852
We've checked the security footage

238
00:23:55,935 --> 00:23:57,520
and will go ahead
and file the insurance claim.

239
00:23:57,603 --> 00:23:59,272
Well, I'll leave it to you then.

240
00:24:09,615 --> 00:24:11,159
Can we talk?

241
00:24:13,161 --> 00:24:15,079
I don't have time right now.
I'm dealing with an emergency.

242
00:24:15,163 --> 00:24:17,957
- Damage control?
- If you know better, please step aside.

243
00:24:18,666 --> 00:24:21,627
Well, we're both busy,
so let's talk on the way.

244
00:24:21,711 --> 00:24:23,921
[pensive music plays]

245
00:24:51,490 --> 00:24:52,950
What is it?

246
00:24:53,034 --> 00:24:55,953
- It was you.
- You told me to set Ms. Han up.

247
00:24:56,037 --> 00:24:58,497
But I never told you
to sabotage the exhibition.

248
00:24:58,581 --> 00:25:01,083
This girl's got more guts than I expected.

249
00:25:02,084 --> 00:25:04,754
In any case,
I'm getting a permanent position, right?

250
00:25:04,837 --> 00:25:06,214
I did just as you said.

251
00:25:06,297 --> 00:25:08,007
[sighs]

252
00:25:08,090 --> 00:25:10,176
How long have you been an intern?

253
00:25:10,259 --> 00:25:11,636
My six months are up next month.

254
00:25:13,137 --> 00:25:15,264
Okay. Okay, but listen.

255
00:25:15,348 --> 00:25:17,975
Just don't slack off,
and make sure you do exactly as I say.

256
00:25:18,059 --> 00:25:19,518
Do you understand?

257
00:25:19,602 --> 00:25:21,979
Yes, I do. But…

258
00:25:22,063 --> 00:25:23,439
But what?

259
00:25:24,023 --> 00:25:27,693
If I get fired, I won't go down alone.

260
00:25:32,406 --> 00:25:34,533
[scoffs, laughs]

261
00:25:35,368 --> 00:25:39,705
Geez, from top to bottom, how did we
only hire brats like her?

262
00:25:41,040 --> 00:25:42,250
Goddamn it!

263
00:25:42,333 --> 00:25:44,669
GANGHA POLICE STATION

264
00:25:44,752 --> 00:25:46,671
YOON SEUNG-JAE
35 YEARS OLD, RESTAURANT CEO

265
00:25:48,256 --> 00:25:50,675
DEATH BY DROWNING

266
00:25:50,758 --> 00:25:55,596
CHOI YOUNG-HO
SUICIDE

267
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:58,057
LEE SU-HO
ACCIDENT

268
00:26:05,439 --> 00:26:08,484
[Gong] What are you trying to do
with a case that's already closed?

269
00:26:09,235 --> 00:26:10,945
These three men follow
the exact same pattern.

270
00:26:11,028 --> 00:26:12,238
Can this really be a coincidence?

271
00:26:13,739 --> 00:26:16,742
Coincidence or not, we know
Han Seol-ah didn't kill Kim Yun-ji.

272
00:26:17,994 --> 00:26:19,453
Could there be an accomplice?

273
00:26:20,454 --> 00:26:22,498
When we reviewed the security footage
and dashcam footage,

274
00:26:22,581 --> 00:26:24,625
we were focused on Han Seol-ah.

275
00:26:24,709 --> 00:26:26,460
There's got to be something we missed.

276
00:26:32,091 --> 00:26:33,926
Do Eun-hye was the one who broke it.

277
00:26:34,010 --> 00:26:35,636
Are we sure it wasn't intentional?

278
00:26:37,138 --> 00:26:40,224
Things like that happen from time to time
on the job. Just a mistake.

279
00:26:43,811 --> 00:26:46,647
- I guess you're always suspicious.
- Yeah.

280
00:26:50,109 --> 00:26:52,403
You're free to have your suspicions

281
00:26:53,821 --> 00:26:55,823
but I won't tolerate you
crossing the line again.

282
00:26:56,574 --> 00:26:57,616
What line is that?

283
00:26:59,452 --> 00:27:00,619
Luen Palace.

284
00:27:00,703 --> 00:27:02,079
[tense music plays]

285
00:27:03,247 --> 00:27:05,583
So? Could you see me well?

286
00:27:07,251 --> 00:27:10,755
[sighs] How long have you known?

287
00:27:17,511 --> 00:27:19,555
LEASE SIGNING FOR LUEN PALACE UNIT 702

288
00:27:41,327 --> 00:27:44,080
[Seol-ah] <i>So you've been</i>
<i>watching me from there all along?</i>

289
00:27:44,955 --> 00:27:47,333
I was just trying to follow
Kim Yun-ji's trail.

290
00:27:48,501 --> 00:27:50,669
So you knew about that apartment too?

291
00:27:53,672 --> 00:27:55,758
I saw you
coming out of that building once.

292
00:27:57,009 --> 00:27:58,719
And you figured it out just from that?

293
00:28:33,295 --> 00:28:34,922
I'm really sorry.

294
00:28:35,798 --> 00:28:37,591
I should've been more careful.

295
00:28:39,718 --> 00:28:42,805
But, uh, could you please reconsider…

296
00:28:42,888 --> 00:28:45,391
Just go announce
that the exhibition's canceled.

297
00:28:48,519 --> 00:28:49,687
Fire it up.

298
00:28:55,818 --> 00:28:57,194
[sorrowful music plays]

299
00:29:04,410 --> 00:29:06,078
[breathes heavily]

300
00:29:09,373 --> 00:29:10,541
[coughing]

301
00:29:22,887 --> 00:29:27,808
I know you're the last person who
wants to give this up right now, Mr. Kim.

302
00:29:28,809 --> 00:29:30,561
But we still have some time left.

303
00:29:30,644 --> 00:29:33,272
You can never make
the same piece twice with glass.

304
00:29:33,355 --> 00:29:34,857
Each piece is unique.

305
00:29:34,940 --> 00:29:36,775
But it's "Twilight Blue," isn't it?

306
00:29:37,985 --> 00:29:42,323
Doesn't the sky at dusk change every
moment? Making it always unique.

307
00:29:45,242 --> 00:29:46,785
What if I can't get the right color?

308
00:29:46,869 --> 00:29:50,498
I'll take full responsibility and cancel
the exhibition if it comes to that.

309
00:29:50,581 --> 00:29:54,084
I'll stay up all night if I have to
and help in every way. Please…

310
00:29:55,252 --> 00:29:56,253
[sighs]

311
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:02,801
[sighs]

312
00:30:07,973 --> 00:30:10,017
Back there,
you'll find cobalt and gold ruby.

313
00:30:10,100 --> 00:30:11,101
Go grab them.

314
00:30:12,895 --> 00:30:14,021
Sure.

315
00:30:24,532 --> 00:30:26,033
COBALT
MARINE BLUE

316
00:30:34,833 --> 00:30:36,001
Thank you.

317
00:30:36,669 --> 00:30:38,337
Did you really have to
get down on your knees?

318
00:30:38,420 --> 00:30:40,089
It could've gone through the insurance.

319
00:30:42,466 --> 00:30:46,178
To an artist,
their work is like their own child.

320
00:30:47,054 --> 00:30:49,431
You poured your blood and sweat,
and now it's gone.

321
00:30:49,515 --> 00:30:51,517
What good is insurance money?

322
00:30:53,060 --> 00:30:56,730
Do you really think
money can erase that pain?

323
00:31:01,694 --> 00:31:03,571
[uplifting music plays]

324
00:31:06,699 --> 00:31:08,367
Here you go, Mr. Kim.

325
00:31:08,951 --> 00:31:10,119
Okay.

326
00:31:11,620 --> 00:31:13,289
Can you bring me that sack?

327
00:31:23,757 --> 00:31:25,259
I'll go grab some coffee.

328
00:31:26,760 --> 00:31:29,597
- Can you give me a hand?
- Sure.

329
00:32:56,308 --> 00:32:57,559
The other way.

330
00:32:58,686 --> 00:32:59,770
[gasps]

331
00:33:01,355 --> 00:33:02,856
[coughs]

332
00:33:19,915 --> 00:33:21,667
[breathes deeply]

333
00:33:40,686 --> 00:33:42,312
[sighs]

334
00:33:55,325 --> 00:33:56,994
How are you feeling?

335
00:33:57,077 --> 00:33:58,287
Are you all right?

336
00:34:00,372 --> 00:34:01,582
I'm okay now.

337
00:34:01,665 --> 00:34:03,459
Oh, man…

338
00:34:05,169 --> 00:34:06,795
[clicks tongue]

339
00:34:06,879 --> 00:34:08,922
I honestly can't figure you out, Ms. Han.

340
00:34:09,798 --> 00:34:12,342
One moment you seem
like you could just let everything go,

341
00:34:12,426 --> 00:34:14,428
and the next,
you won't give up on a thing.

342
00:34:16,263 --> 00:34:20,768
You seem strong, yet at times,
it feels like you're barely holding on.

343
00:34:22,811 --> 00:34:27,149
So what? Does that earn me any sympathy?

344
00:34:28,776 --> 00:34:30,360
[gentle music plays]

345
00:34:30,444 --> 00:34:34,823
At first, I wondered if it was the
insurance money that you were after.

346
00:34:36,158 --> 00:34:39,912
Or maybe it was those three men's deaths
that you truly wanted.

347
00:34:41,413 --> 00:34:45,667
But now I wonder if you're just a victim,

348
00:34:45,751 --> 00:34:48,128
and I'm the one doing
something terrible to you.

349
00:34:50,464 --> 00:34:52,341
I couldn't help but feel guilty.

350
00:34:56,553 --> 00:34:58,388
Now, I must find out

351
00:34:59,765 --> 00:35:03,101
why such misfortune
keeps befalling Han Seol-ah.

352
00:35:09,149 --> 00:35:12,986
You said there is no such thing
as a third coincidence.

353
00:35:16,698 --> 00:35:20,953
That's when it all became clear to me too
that something wasn't right.

354
00:35:23,121 --> 00:35:27,709
So someone specifically targeted
Han Seol-ah's men and killed them?

355
00:35:29,211 --> 00:35:30,420
Possibly?

356
00:35:32,297 --> 00:35:33,590
Do you have any guesses?

357
00:35:33,674 --> 00:35:35,884
I need to know in order to help you.

358
00:35:37,094 --> 00:35:38,303
Do you…

359
00:35:39,763 --> 00:35:41,348
really trust me?

360
00:35:44,184 --> 00:35:46,061
I want to try trusting you.

361
00:35:47,354 --> 00:35:48,981
Han Seol-ah.

362
00:35:50,232 --> 00:35:51,775
I want to trust you.

363
00:36:15,340 --> 00:36:16,842
[alarm system beeping]

364
00:36:18,594 --> 00:36:20,012
Cha Woo-seok!

365
00:36:35,152 --> 00:36:36,737
<i>The phone you are trying to reach</i>
<i>is turned off.</i>

366
00:36:36,820 --> 00:36:39,031
<i>You will be directed to voicemail</i>
<i>after the beep…</i>

367
00:36:40,073 --> 00:36:43,035
What's going on?
I can't reach him, and he's not home.

368
00:36:53,170 --> 00:36:54,922
{\an8}KIM YUN-JI
AUCTIONEER AT ROYAL AUCTION

369
00:36:55,005 --> 00:36:56,673
BURNER PHONE

370
00:36:56,757 --> 00:36:58,508
[pensive music plays]

371
00:37:24,034 --> 00:37:25,619
HAN SEOL-AH(34).M4A

372
00:37:25,702 --> 00:37:28,497
[Seol-ah, on recording]
<i>I don't have the right to fall apart.</i>

373
00:37:28,580 --> 00:37:32,459
<i>Instead of my parents,</i>
<i>I'm the one who survived.</i>

374
00:37:33,794 --> 00:37:35,212
[Suk-ji, on recording] <i>Just cry.</i>

375
00:37:49,267 --> 00:37:50,894
[alarm system beeping]

376
00:37:53,814 --> 00:37:54,815
[door closes]

377
00:37:56,525 --> 00:37:58,235
Another stakeout around here?

378
00:37:58,318 --> 00:38:00,529
Sorry for coming in when you weren't home.

379
00:38:01,321 --> 00:38:03,115
Why? It's nothing new.

380
00:38:05,534 --> 00:38:07,077
You said you were going
to the auction house.

381
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:09,204
What happened? Your phone was off.

382
00:38:09,287 --> 00:38:12,290
I had to run out of town and
didn't get a chance to charge my phone.

383
00:38:13,542 --> 00:38:14,626
With Han Seol-ah?

384
00:38:16,628 --> 00:38:17,629
Yeah.

385
00:38:19,214 --> 00:38:24,136
You know, maybe the real culprit
is someone else in Han Seol-ah's circle…

386
00:38:29,725 --> 00:38:31,351
Do you feel bad for that woman?

387
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:33,311
What?

388
00:38:38,650 --> 00:38:41,403
I bet you felt sympathy
after listening to this.

389
00:38:42,612 --> 00:38:46,700
"Maybe she's not the culprit.
She must've been in pain and struggling."

390
00:38:47,492 --> 00:38:49,494
And then the obsession started.

391
00:38:49,578 --> 00:38:51,621
What obsession?

392
00:38:51,705 --> 00:38:53,457
I just want to know the truth here.

393
00:38:53,540 --> 00:38:56,001
Do you know why you're so intent
on finding the truth?

394
00:38:58,003 --> 00:39:02,007
It's just because you hope
she's not the culprit.

395
00:39:05,719 --> 00:39:07,471
This counts as evidence tampering.

396
00:39:07,554 --> 00:39:09,431
You're interfering with an investigation.

397
00:39:11,725 --> 00:39:15,020
I can't let this slide.
I'm doing this by the book.

398
00:39:17,230 --> 00:39:18,899
[dramatic music plays]

399
00:39:25,614 --> 00:39:26,823
[sighs]

400
00:39:39,878 --> 00:39:40,879
{\an8}HAN SEOL-AH

401
00:39:45,467 --> 00:39:49,387
[Woo-seok] <i>So someone</i>
<i>specifically targeted Han Seol-ah's men</i>

402
00:39:49,471 --> 00:39:50,472
<i>and killed them?</i>

403
00:39:54,601 --> 00:39:56,853
<i>Anyone who loves Han Seol-ah dies.</i>

404
00:39:58,021 --> 00:39:59,898
{\an8}YOON SEUNG-JAE

405
00:39:59,981 --> 00:40:02,359
{\an8}CHOI YOUNG-HO

406
00:40:02,442 --> 00:40:04,736
{\an8}LEE SU-HO

407
00:40:04,820 --> 00:40:08,323
<i>Someone new will die as well. A new victim</i>

408
00:40:12,577 --> 00:40:13,995
<i>But that man…</i>

409
00:40:15,789 --> 00:40:17,582
<i>can find out the truth.</i>

410
00:40:35,559 --> 00:40:38,687
Huh? Oh. Look at this.

411
00:40:39,688 --> 00:40:41,356
[dramatic music plays]

412
00:40:45,193 --> 00:40:48,071
This was caught on the security camera
near the auction house.

413
00:40:49,531 --> 00:40:52,742
Judging by this angle,
he was filming the rooftop.

414
00:40:52,826 --> 00:40:54,161
We'll have to track him down.

415
00:40:54,244 --> 00:40:56,204
Hey, Gong. You're on fire.

416
00:40:58,331 --> 00:40:59,457
Look right here.

417
00:41:01,877 --> 00:41:05,297
CAPTURING LIGHT:
KIM JOON-YOUNG SPECIAL EXHIBITION

418
00:41:12,179 --> 00:41:15,432
The artist asked for all
the broken pieces to be displayed

419
00:41:15,515 --> 00:41:17,684
as part of the exhibition.

420
00:41:17,767 --> 00:41:19,853
He also said there's no need for a claim.

421
00:41:21,396 --> 00:41:22,689
[sighs]

422
00:41:24,274 --> 00:41:27,986
He said that he wanted to show
that light cannot be trapped.

423
00:41:28,069 --> 00:41:29,362
Hmm…

424
00:41:31,198 --> 00:41:33,992
Thank you for that day.

425
00:41:36,411 --> 00:41:37,662
Oh…

426
00:41:39,956 --> 00:41:43,418
Ah, you know, I've been thinking,

427
00:41:44,961 --> 00:41:46,504
if what you said is true,

428
00:41:46,588 --> 00:41:48,965
it means the culprit targeted those men.

429
00:41:49,716 --> 00:41:51,718
It's probably someone who knows me well.

430
00:41:51,801 --> 00:41:53,678
Every crime has a motive.

431
00:41:54,971 --> 00:41:56,014
What could this be?

432
00:41:58,808 --> 00:42:00,060
My misery?

433
00:42:04,105 --> 00:42:05,523
To find out…

434
00:42:07,442 --> 00:42:11,029
Han Seol-ah has to meet a new man.

435
00:42:11,780 --> 00:42:13,281
[dramatic music plays]

436
00:42:14,950 --> 00:42:17,035
If the culprit thinks I'm your boyfriend,

437
00:42:17,953 --> 00:42:22,332
I'll end up dead,
or I'll find out who the killer is.

438
00:42:30,048 --> 00:42:31,633
Let's do it.

439
00:42:33,343 --> 00:42:34,678
Do you mean that?

440
00:42:34,761 --> 00:42:39,432
Now, I'm really curious what kind
of face you'll make

441
00:42:39,516 --> 00:42:42,519
when you learn the truth and look at me.

442
00:43:39,034 --> 00:43:40,994
[secretary] The auctioneer is here, sir.

443
00:43:59,429 --> 00:44:03,099
- Welcome.
- Thank you for your invitation, Mr. Paek.

444
00:44:03,183 --> 00:44:06,186
I'm really touched
that you came in person.

445
00:44:07,479 --> 00:44:09,898
I have you to thank
for giving me this opportunity.

446
00:44:11,316 --> 00:44:12,776
I'm a little late.

447
00:44:17,030 --> 00:44:20,241
My name is Cha Woo-seok. I manage
your insurance account.

448
00:44:26,831 --> 00:44:29,084
Nice to meet you. I'm Paek Jun-beom.

449
00:44:29,793 --> 00:44:31,252
I guess you're left-handed.

450
00:44:32,253 --> 00:44:35,006
Oh, it's just a habit of mine.

451
00:44:35,840 --> 00:44:38,885
I like the left hand too.
It's the closest to the heart.

452
00:44:56,861 --> 00:45:00,740
I think it'll look empty
when that spot's left bare.

453
00:45:01,741 --> 00:45:07,414
It's said that letting go brings in the
chance to welcome new things to your life.

454
00:45:09,416 --> 00:45:12,168
So, I picked out a few pieces
as alternatives.

455
00:45:12,252 --> 00:45:14,421
There's no fee for this, of course.

456
00:45:21,636 --> 00:45:23,263
Hmm, just as I thought.

457
00:45:24,931 --> 00:45:29,269
You've got a knack for picking great art
and reading people well.

458
00:45:33,148 --> 00:45:35,316
This will probably take a while.

459
00:45:35,400 --> 00:45:36,818
How about a glass of wine?

460
00:45:55,962 --> 00:45:58,298
The Stiller piece
has well-documented provenance.

461
00:45:58,882 --> 00:46:02,302
Is there a specific reason
for the insurance company to check it?

462
00:46:03,178 --> 00:46:07,223
Since it's such a high-value piece,
there are protocols that must be followed.

463
00:46:09,350 --> 00:46:12,937
The truth is, I'm a bit of a skeptic.

464
00:46:15,815 --> 00:46:19,986
Insurance is able to turn both art
and human life into money,

465
00:46:21,779 --> 00:46:24,699
and I've seen too many people
give up their humanity because of it.

466
00:46:25,992 --> 00:46:27,952
[tense music plays]

467
00:46:29,537 --> 00:46:32,832
Money brings out
the real nature of people.

468
00:46:34,542 --> 00:46:37,504
Or also, we're all seeing things

469
00:46:37,587 --> 00:46:38,922
only from our own perspective.

470
00:46:46,221 --> 00:46:50,308
Anyway, that's sad.
You have trouble trusting people.

471
00:46:50,391 --> 00:46:51,768
It must be a bit lonely.

472
00:46:53,269 --> 00:46:54,395
[snorts]

473
00:46:54,479 --> 00:46:56,439
If I want to trust someone, I trust them…

474
00:46:59,067 --> 00:47:00,610
without running the numbers.

475
00:47:01,945 --> 00:47:03,821
I just follow my heart.

476
00:47:17,877 --> 00:47:18,878
[scoffs]

477
00:47:34,727 --> 00:47:36,646
I noticed the logo on the business card.

478
00:47:36,729 --> 00:47:37,897
Does it mean anything?

479
00:47:38,898 --> 00:47:41,526
I'm not really sure, but my boss liked it.

480
00:48:04,173 --> 00:48:05,800
[ringing tone]

481
00:48:07,552 --> 00:48:08,970
Name is Paek Jun-beom.

482
00:48:09,053 --> 00:48:11,306
Dig up everything you can on him.

483
00:48:12,265 --> 00:48:15,768
Boss? Hello? Hello…

484
00:48:17,061 --> 00:48:19,939
Ugh, what the hell? Like I'm just
gonna dig and find this stuff?

485
00:48:20,023 --> 00:48:21,482
That lowlife doesn't even cover the costs.

486
00:48:21,566 --> 00:48:22,900
MESSAGE

487
00:48:24,777 --> 00:48:26,821
DEPOSIT: 1,000,000 WON
CHA WOO-SEOK

488
00:48:26,904 --> 00:48:29,115
No, he's not a lowlife at all.

489
00:48:30,617 --> 00:48:34,662
[groans] Paek Jun-beom. Okay.

490
00:48:38,708 --> 00:48:40,043
[Jun-beom exhales deeply]

491
00:48:40,752 --> 00:48:42,211
Now it's really hitting me.

492
00:48:44,297 --> 00:48:45,423
Does it feel empty?

493
00:48:46,549 --> 00:48:48,051
But it's also a relief.

494
00:48:49,802 --> 00:48:53,598
That piece came to me
for a particular reason.

495
00:48:59,354 --> 00:49:02,231
Perhaps so that we could meet.

496
00:49:03,858 --> 00:49:05,693
[pensive music plays]

497
00:49:12,784 --> 00:49:17,205
My feelings are sincere enough
to give you Stiller.

498
00:49:19,540 --> 00:49:21,709
I don't expect an answer right away.

499
00:49:23,294 --> 00:49:26,381
I just wanted to tell you
before it's too late.

500
00:49:34,347 --> 00:49:35,807
Looks like it's a bit late.

501
00:49:38,768 --> 00:49:40,144
We need to check the piece in.

502
00:49:53,116 --> 00:49:55,076
This business deal is important to me.

503
00:49:56,244 --> 00:49:57,745
Wasn't I supposed to be Han Seol-ah's man?

504
00:49:58,329 --> 00:50:00,248
I didn't realize I had to wait in line.

505
00:50:02,458 --> 00:50:03,793
Don't jump to conclusions.

506
00:50:06,629 --> 00:50:07,922
If that's not it,

507
00:50:09,340 --> 00:50:11,300
then what's your reason for testing him?

508
00:50:13,636 --> 00:50:15,304
Because he seems to know you real well?

509
00:50:17,515 --> 00:50:18,808
Do you find that guy suspicious?

510
00:50:23,229 --> 00:50:24,772
Then let's find out right now.

511
00:50:38,703 --> 00:50:40,455
Let's do this right then.

512
00:51:23,247 --> 00:51:26,000
The ball's been thrown.
Let's see if he reacts.

513
00:51:29,712 --> 00:51:31,422
[dramatic music plays]

514
00:53:28,372 --> 00:53:30,166
Just a touch more light on the red…

515
00:53:35,755 --> 00:53:39,050
Eun-hyuk, can we take a look without
cropping the frames on either side?

516
00:53:46,182 --> 00:53:48,935
Hey, what's going on that we need
to meet in the meeting room?

517
00:53:52,146 --> 00:53:54,857
Once a company shuts down,
there aren't any records.

518
00:53:54,941 --> 00:53:56,484
I need your network for this.

519
00:53:56,567 --> 00:53:59,862
{\an8}ELECTRONIC RECORDS FOR GW LIFE INSURANCE
DO NOT EXIST DUE TO ITS BANKRUPTCY

520
00:53:59,946 --> 00:54:01,697
[sighs] Right,

521
00:54:01,781 --> 00:54:04,367
as an insurance investigator,
you have to check this.

522
00:54:05,618 --> 00:54:06,744
[clicks tongue]

523
00:54:28,516 --> 00:54:31,560
- Thank you. I'll just take a quick look.
- Yes. Sure.

524
00:55:05,219 --> 00:55:08,347
[Woo-seok] <i>Maybe the real culprit</i>
<i>is someone else in Han Seol-ah's circle…</i>

525
00:55:08,431 --> 00:55:10,766
[Joo-young] <i>Do you know why</i>
<i>you're so intent on finding the truth?</i>

526
00:55:11,517 --> 00:55:15,646
It's just because you hope
she's not the culprit.

527
00:55:16,647 --> 00:55:17,982
What?

528
00:55:30,953 --> 00:55:32,413
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

529
00:55:38,878 --> 00:55:39,879
[clicks tongue]

530
00:55:44,175 --> 00:55:47,928
- What is it?
- Well, here's what you asked for.

531
00:55:48,804 --> 00:55:50,181
Take a look, and you'll see.

532
00:55:50,264 --> 00:55:52,808
These are old records.
They were hard to dig up.

533
00:56:01,734 --> 00:56:02,860
[sighs]

534
00:56:06,363 --> 00:56:07,531
Oh…

535
00:56:10,618 --> 00:56:11,660
What's going on now?

536
00:56:13,120 --> 00:56:16,624
Well, I think he got hit right here.

537
00:56:16,707 --> 00:56:19,293
- Right here? Like this?
- No, no.

538
00:56:19,376 --> 00:56:20,753
Like this.

539
00:56:23,214 --> 00:56:24,840
[dramatic music plays]

540
00:56:25,549 --> 00:56:27,384
[engine revs]

541
00:56:33,015 --> 00:56:34,809
[tires screech]

542
00:56:38,187 --> 00:56:39,396
[screaming on video]

543
00:56:39,480 --> 00:56:42,817
This video was captured by
a witness at the scene of the incident.

544
00:56:44,318 --> 00:56:46,362
VIP INVITATION SPECIAL AUCTION…

545
00:56:53,244 --> 00:56:55,871
Did you see? On the rooftop.

546
00:57:03,045 --> 00:57:05,089
{\an8}VIP INVITATION SPECIAL AUCTION
AUGUST 26, 2025 - ROYAL AUCTION

547
00:57:11,929 --> 00:57:13,514
Oh, that's…

548
00:57:16,475 --> 00:57:20,437
There was someone else on the rooftop.

549
00:57:30,948 --> 00:57:32,366
[knocking at door]

550
00:57:34,577 --> 00:57:36,662
What brings you here at this…

551
00:57:53,137 --> 00:57:55,139
You found out something else.

552
00:58:07,693 --> 00:58:09,612
{\an8}INSURANCE PAYOUT STATEMENT

553
00:58:10,404 --> 00:58:11,739
Two months before the fire,

554
00:58:11,822 --> 00:58:14,491
the artist happened
to take out life insurance.

555
00:58:15,868 --> 00:58:17,369
Payout went to his daughter.

556
00:58:18,871 --> 00:58:21,373
She used the money to pay off
his high-interest loans.

557
00:58:31,258 --> 00:58:32,801
This is even more surprising.

558
00:58:34,970 --> 00:58:37,056
The mother also had life insurance,

559
00:58:38,891 --> 00:58:41,101
and the payout went to the daughter.

560
00:58:41,185 --> 00:58:42,311
POLICYHOLDER: PARK YUN-JEONG
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH

561
00:58:42,394 --> 00:58:43,896
140,000.

562
00:58:53,405 --> 00:58:55,908
You knew your parents
had life insurance, didn't you?

563
00:59:00,788 --> 00:59:03,916
Han Seol-ah, you were at the scene
and are the only survivor.

564
00:59:08,212 --> 00:59:09,922
Even if no one else knows…

565
00:59:11,924 --> 00:59:13,842
you know the truth.

566
00:59:13,926 --> 00:59:15,928
[sorrowful music plays]

567
00:59:29,858 --> 00:59:31,568
Who started the fire?

568
00:59:39,618 --> 00:59:40,828
It can't be.

569
00:59:45,499 --> 00:59:46,625
That's right.

570
00:59:50,796 --> 00:59:52,423
[dramatic music plays]

571
01:00:08,772 --> 01:00:10,232
I did it.

572
01:00:12,985 --> 01:00:14,570
I killed them.

573
01:00:18,157 --> 01:00:19,199
[gasps]

574
01:00:21,910 --> 01:00:23,620
[dramatic music plays]

575
01:01:04,661 --> 01:01:08,874
{\an8}[Woo-seok] <i>As if you were asking me</i>
<i>to uncover the truth.</i>

576
01:01:08,957 --> 01:01:10,334
{\an8}[Seol-ah] <i>It was my choice.</i>

577
01:01:10,417 --> 01:01:12,628
{\an8}Are you sure you're not letting your
emotions keep you from seeing the truth?

578
01:01:12,711 --> 01:01:14,463
{\an8}[Woo-seok] <i>What if I'm truly worried?</i>

579
01:01:14,546 --> 01:01:15,881
{\an8}Were you following me?

580
01:01:15,964 --> 01:01:19,760
{\an8}You wanted me to trust you,
isn't that right?

581
01:01:19,843 --> 01:01:24,139
{\an8}[Joo-young] <i>This is the person Ms.</i>
<i>Kim Yun-ji was last seen with that day.</i>

582
01:01:24,223 --> 01:01:27,643
{\an8}If he's the one who killed those men,
there's only one answer.

583
01:01:28,143 --> 01:01:30,604
{\an8}- He wants Han Seol-ah.
- No!

584
01:01:30,687 --> 01:01:32,314
{\an8}[Woo-seok] <i>I no longer suspect you.</i>

585
01:01:32,898 --> 01:01:37,361
{\an8}[Seol-ah] <i>But in the end,</i>
<i>won't uncover anything at all.</i>

